# Coding Standards

## Principles
- **Smallest safe change** — extend, don't rewrite working modules
- **Reuse** — search for existing `fmt`, `toast`, `render*` before adding helpers
- **No unnecessary abstraction** — no frameworks, no build step unless approved
- **Backward compatible** — family URL and `bills.json` schema must keep working

## Patterns
```javascript
// ✅ Currency
fmt(amount)

// ✅ DOM updates — escape user content
function esc(s) { const d = document.createElement('div'); d.textContent = s; return d.innerHTML; }

// ❌ Never inject user note/raw input via innerHTML unescaped
el.innerHTML = `<td>${b.note}</td>`  // XSS risk

// ✅ Errors — prefer toast over alert
toast("✅ Saved!");

// ❌ Silent failures
catch (e) {}
```

## File sync
After editing `index.html`:
1. Copy → `hospital-bills.html`
2. Bump `PAGE_VERSION`, `version.json`, `refresh.html` `?b=`, `<head>` cache script

## Naming
- Match existing: `fmt`, `fmtDate`, `sumWho`, `computeSettlement`
- Telugu UI strings OK in templates; logic comments in English

## Dead code
Do not add new dead code. Flag existing dead code in `TECH_DEBT.md`; don't remove without approval.
